{{Infobox language |name=Aghem |altname=Wum |nativename=Yum |states=[[Cameroon]] |region=[[Menchum]] |speakers=27,000 |date=2000 |ref=e18 |familycolor=Niger-Congo |fam2=[[Atlantic–Congo]] |fam3=[[Benue–Congo]] |fam4=[[Southern Bantoid]] |fam5=[[Grassfields languages|Grassfields]] |fam6=[[Ring languages|Ring]] |fam7=West |iso3=agq |glotto=aghe1239 |glottorefname=Aghem }}
'''Aghem''' (Wum or Yum) is a [[Grassfields Bantu language]] spoken in the [[Wum]] Central Sub-division in [[Menchum]] Division of the North West Region of [[Cameroon]].
