The '''Brisbane Women's Club''' is a club for women, one of the first in [[Brisbane]], [[Queensland]], Australia.<ref name=awr>{{cite web|title=Brisbane Women's Club (1908–)|url=http://www.womenaustralia.info/biogs/PR00162b.htm|website=The Australian Women's Register|accessdate=1 December 2014}}</ref>
==History== The club was founded in 1908 as the Progressive Women's Club, an offshoot of the [[Queensland Women's Electoral League]]. Its aims were both political and philanthropic.<ref name=awr/><ref>{{cite news |url=http://nla.gov.au/nla.news-article19533513 |title=WOMEN'S PROGRESSIVE CLUB. |newspaper=[[The Brisbane Courier]] |date=3 April 1908 |accessdate=2 December 2014 |page=7 |publisher=National Library of Australia}}</ref> In 1912, it was renamed the Brisbane Women's Club.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://nla.gov.au/nla.news-article19730437 |title=WOMAN'S WORLD. |newspaper=[[The Brisbane Courier]] |date=4 May 1912 |accessdate=2 December 2014 |page=7 |publisher=National Library of Australia}}</ref>
