{{Infobox Governor |name= Delbar Jan Arman Shinwari |image= Del Bar Jan Arman.jpg |imagesize = 225px | |caption= |order= |office= [[List of governors of Badghis|Governor of Badghis]], [[Afghanistan]] |term_start= 30 March 2009 |term_end= 19 September 2012 |lieutenant= |predecessor= [[Mohammad Ashraf Naseri]] |successor= Mohammad Tahir Sabari |birth_date= |birth_place=[[Jaji Maidan District|Jaji Maidan]], [[Khost Province|Khost]], [[Afghanistan]] |death_date= |death_place= |spouse= |profession= |party= |religion= [[Muslim]] | order2=[[List of governors of Zabul|Governor of Zabul]], [[Afghanistan]]. | term_start2=6 March 2005 | term_end2=30 March 2009 | predecessor2=[[Khial Mohammad]] | successor2=[[Mohammad Ashraf Naseri]] }}
'''Delbar Jan Arman''', also '''Dilbar Jan Arman Shinwari''' ({{lang-ps|'''دلبر جان ارمان شینواری'''}}) is a politician from [[Jaji Maidan District|Jaji Maidan]] district of [[Khost Province|Khost]], [[Afghanistan]].<ref name="NPS">http://www.nps.edu/programs/ccs/Docs/Executive%20Summaries/Zabul_Prov_Overview_CCS.pdf</ref> He is the ex-governor of [[Badghis Province]].
Delbar Jan Arman has a military and academic background. In the 1970s, he studied for six years at the American Technical College, [[Kabul]]. He was also trained in the [[Afghan Army]].
From 2005 till 2009 he was the governor of [[Zabul Province]], [[Afghanistan]]. He was an anti-Soviet insurgent who fled to Pakistan during the [[Taliban]]'s rule of Afghanistan. He was appointed [[List of governors of Zabul|governor of Zabul]] on 3 March 2005 by President [[Hamid Karzai]]. Delbar Jan Arman is known for his intimate involvement with the U.S. [[Provincial Reconstruction Team]] based in [[Qalat (Zabul)|Qalat]] and their combined efforts to quickly deploy development projects across the province.<ref name="USATODAY">{{cite news|url=https://www.usatoday.com/news/world/2006-07-11-rumsfeld_x.htm?POE=NEWISVA|newspaper=USA Today|date=11 July 2006|agency=AP|title=Rumsfeld says NATO buildup in Afghanistan does not mean U.S. departure}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last=Blanchfield |first=Mike |title=Afghanistan air force |url=https://nationalpost.com/story.html?id=443513 |newspaper=National Post |date=14 April 2008 }}{{dead link|date=December 2016 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref> In May 2009 he switched positions with [[Mohammad Ashraf Naseri]]. Delbar Jan Arman became governor of [[Badghis Province]], Mohammad Ashraf Naseri took overt the Government of [[Zabul Province]].
