{{Unreferenced|date=June 2015}} '''Mizmar''' ({{lang-ar|مزمار}}) is an [[Africa]]n [[dance]].. The dance involves moving while twirling a [[bamboo]] [[Walking stick|cane]], to the music of drums. The dance and music have strong [[Bantu peoples|Bantu]] influences. In the past, the ritual was associated with spiritual healing practices, similar to [[Fann At-Tanbura]].
