{{distinguish|Languages of New Caledonia}} {{Infobox language family |name=New Caledonian |altname= |region=[[New Caledonia]] |familycolor=Austronesian |fam2=[[Malayo-Polynesian languages|Malayo-Polynesian]] |fam3=[[Oceanic languages|Oceanic]] |fam4=[[Southern Oceanic languages|Southern Oceanic]] |glotto=newc1243 |glottorefname=New Caledonian |fam5=New Caledonian-Loyalties}}
The thirty '''New Caledonian languages''' form a branch of the [[Southern Oceanic languages]]. Their speakers are known as [[Kanak people|Kanaks]]. One language is extinct, one is critically endangered, 4 are severely endangered, 5 are endangered, and another 5 are vulnerable to extinction.
== Languages == [[File:Langueskanak.jpg|thumb|450px|Populations of the native languages of New Caledonia. Grey, green, and red are the languages of the New Caledonian branch.]]
